toward the poles. Ice sheets covered much of North America and northwest Eurasia,
and sea level was commensurately lower. Atmospheric CO

regions; the atmosphere was dustier, and ranges of many plant species contracted
into glacial refugia; forest extent and coral reef distribution was reduced worldwide.
